    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-01-22T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-01-22T17:00:00-05:00" n="40"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/79a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-01-22T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 22, 1926—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. The protracted debate in the Senate on the World Court issue<note n="50"
                        xml:id="d40fn50">See <ref target="#pg_1">pp. 1</ref> ff.</note> may delay
                    action on the appropriation for the Disarmament Commission beyond February 1.
                    For this reason it is important that Department be informed at earliest possible
                    date whether repeated press rumors of postponement of Preparatory Commission’s
                    meeting are accurate and if they are, when definite notification of postponement
                    will be received and the new date fixed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
